wlsrMIB.name: wlsrMIB
wlsrMIB.contactinfo: Postal: 1322 Crossman Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: dl-support@arubanetworks.com Phone: +1 408 227 4500
wlsrMIB.description: This MIB is for managing the Access Points and Air Monitors.

wlsrConfigTable.name: wlsrConfigTable
wlsrConfigTable.description: Table will list the configuration data of a wifi interface.

wlsrMode.name: wlsrMode
wlsrMode.description: Mode of the Access Point. Master indicates that we are operating as Access Point. monitor indicates that the AP is an Air Monitor.

wlsrCurrentChannel.name: wlsrCurrentChannel
wlsrCurrentChannel.description: The current operating frequency channel of the DSSS PHY.

wlsrTxPower.name: wlsrTxPower
wlsrTxPower.description: Transmit power of the Access point. The value is between 0 ... 4

wlsrRTSThreshold.name: wlsrRTSThreshold
wlsrRTSThreshold.description: This attribute shall indicate the number of octets in an MPDU, below which an RTS/CTS handshake shall not be performed.

wlsrRetryLimit.name: wlsrRetryLimit
wlsrRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to dot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 7.

wlsrPreamble.name: wlsrPreamble
wlsrPreamble.description: The current radio preamble type in use by the wifi interface.

wlsrBeaconInterval.name: wlsrBeaconInterval
wlsrBeaconInterval.description: This object shall specify the number of TU that a station shall use for scheduling Beacon transmissions. This value is transmitted in Beacon and Probe Response frames.

wlsrPowerMgmt.name: wlsrPowerMgmt
wlsrPowerMgmt.description: This attribute indicates whether Power Management is enabled or not.

wlsrLoadBalance.name: wlsrLoadBalance
wlsrLoadBalance.description: This attribute indicates if load balancing is enabled or disabled.

wlsrSupportedRates.name: wlsrSupportedRates
wlsrSupportedRates.description: Basic Bit rates supported by this WIFI interface.

wlsrDTIMPeriod.name: wlsrDTIMPeriod
wlsrDTIMPeriod.description: This attribute shall specify the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a TIM element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the DTIM Period field of Beacon frames.

wlsrLMSAddress.name: wlsrLMSAddress
wlsrLMSAddress.description: This attribute indicates the IP Address of the Local switch that the AP is connected to.

wlsrEncryption.name: wlsrEncryption
wlsrEncryption.description: This attribute indicates the Encryption type of the WIFI interface.

wlsrStatus.name: wlsrStatus
wlsrStatus.description: This attribute indicates the status of the WIFI Interface.

wlsrAgeout.name: wlsrAgeout
wlsrAgeout.description: This attribute indicates the ageout value in seconds.

wlsrMTU.name: wlsrMTU
wlsrMTU.description: This attribute indicates the MTU of the WIFI Interface.

wlsrLocation.name: wlsrLocation
wlsrLocation.description: This attribute indicates the Location of the Access Point in Building.Floor.location format.

wlsrHideSSID.name: wlsrHideSSID
wlsrHideSSID.description: This attribute indicates if SSID is hidden or not.

wlsrDenyBroadcast.name: wlsrDenyBroadcast
wlsrDenyBroadcast.description: A True value indicates that Broadcast is disabled.

wlsrBGmode.name: wlsrBGmode
wlsrBGmode.description: This attributes indicates the mode of the WIFI Interface

wlsrCardType.name: wlsrCardType
wlsrCardType.description: Indicates the type of the radio card.

wlsrRegDomain.name: wlsrRegDomain
wlsrRegDomain.description: This Object represents the configured Regulatory Domain this AP will adhere to. 1 -- US 2 -- JAPAN 3 -- EU 4 -- EU2 5 -- EU3 6 -- KOREA 7 -- CHINA 8 -- France 9 -- Singapore 10 -- MALAY 11 -- BRAZIL 12 -- Taiwan 13 -- Czech Republic 14 -- GR 15 -- South Africa 16 -- Argentina 17 -- Australia 18 -- Chile

wlsrCountryCode.name: wlsrCountryCode
wlsrCountryCode.description: This Object represents the configured Country code .

wlsrTxRates.name: wlsrTxRates
wlsrTxRates.description: Transmit Bit rates supported by this WIFI interface.
